discussion_comments.comment_body:
I like it!
But I think better place is [LikeC4ProjectConfig](https://github.com/likec4/likec4/blob/072d27f866b794e76a34af181a1e41446b1ca261/packages/config/src/schema.ts#L20)
It enables incremental adoption per-project. But more important - I have feature-flag env var and push sources, but my colleague/CI does not - we have "works on my machine" problem, don't we?

We can introduce smth like

```ts
export const LikeC4ExperimentalSchema = z.object({
  dynamicViewBranches: z
    .boolean()
    .optional()
    .meta({
      description: "....."
    })
})

export const LikeC4ProjectJsonConfigSchema = z.object({
  //...
  experimental: LikeC4ExperimentalSchema.optional()
})
```

Project configuration comes with [`LikeC4Model`](https://github.com/likec4/likec4/blob/072d27f866b794e76a34af181a1e41446b1ca261/packages/core/src/model/LikeC4Model.ts#L336) (and populated [here](https://github.com/likec4/likec4/blob/072d27f866b794e76a34af181a1e41446b1ca261/packages/language-server/src/model/builder/buildModel.ts#L244-L248)). Duplication in core's [LikeC4Project](https://github.com/likec4/likec4/blob/072d27f866b794e76a34af181a1e41446b1ca261/packages/core/src/types/project.ts#L24) unavoidable (`config` depends on `core`), temp trade-off.

`DynamicViewCompute` gets `LikeC4Model` as argument, there you get project configuration as well

